definition.value: A quercetin sulfate with a sulfo group at position 3.
The ring-opened aldehydo-form of D-galactose 6-phosphate.
A deuterated isotopologue of caffeine in which the nine hydrogens contained in the 1, 3, and 7 methyl groups are substituted with deuterium.
A carbopolyclic compound comprising of four carbocyclic rings.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 3',2'-cGAMP; major species at pH 7.3.
A composition-only glycan consisting of four hexosyl groups, three acetaminohexosyl groups and three 6-deoxyhexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex4 HexNAc3 dHex3.

A composition-only glycan consisting of seven hexosyl groups, ten acetaminohexosyl groups, one 6-deoxyhexosyl group and four N-acetyl-neuraminic acid groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex7 HexNAc10 dHex1 NeuAc4.

A composition-only glycan consisting of four hexosyl groups, two acetaminohexosyl groups and one N-acetyl-neuraminic acid group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex4 HexNAc2 NeuAc1.
A composition-only glycan consisting of ten hexosyl groups and one acetaminohexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex10 HexNAc1.
A composition-only glycan consisting of five hexosyl groups and eight acetaminohexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex5 HexNAc8.
A composition-only glycan consisting of six hexosyl groups, six acetaminohexosyl groups and two 6-deoxyhexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex6 HexNAc6 dHex2.

A composition-only glycan consisting of one hexosyl group, three acetaminohexosyl groups, one 6-deoxyhexosyl group and one N-acetyl-neuraminic acid group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex1 HexNAc3 dHex1 NeuAc1.

A composition-only glycan consisting of three hexosyl groups, two acetaminohexosyl groups and two N-acetyl-neuraminic acid group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex3 HexNAc2 NeuAc2.
A composition-only glycan consisting of two hexosyl groups and one acetaminohexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex2 HexNAc1.
A composition-only glycan consisting of one hexosyl group, two acetaminohexosyl groups and two 6-deoxyhexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex1 HexNAc2 dHex2.
A composition-only glycan consisting of six hexosyl groups and one acetaminohexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex6 HexNAc1.
A composition-only glycan consisting of three hexosyl groups, one acetaminohexosyl group and one 6-deoxyhexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex3 HexNAc1 dHex1.
A composition-only glycan consisting of three hexosyl groups, nine acetaminohexosyl groups and one 6-deoxyhexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex3 HexNAc9 dHex1.
A member of the class of dimethylanilines that is N,N-dimethylaniline in which the tertiary amino group has been oxidised to give the corresponding N-oxide.
A composition-only glycan consisting of five hexosyl groups, four acetaminohexosyl groups and four 6-deoxyhexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex5 HexNAc4 dHex4.
A composition-only glycan consisting of one acetaminohexosyl group and one N-glycolyl-neuraminic acid group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: HexNAc1 NeuGc1.
A thiazolidinemonocarboxylic acid that is 1,3-thiazolidine substituted by a carboxy group at position 2.
A carbopolyclic compound comprising of five carbocyclic rings.

A member of the class of isoindoles that is 4,7-dihydro-2H-isoindole substituted by methyl, oxo, methylamino, and oxo groups at positions 1, 4, 5, and 7, respectively. It is produced by heterologous expression of the fluostatin biosynthetic gene cluster from the marine derived Micromonospora rosaria SCSIO N160 in Streptomyces albus J1074.

A member of the class of isoquinolines that is 5,8-dihydroisoquinoline substituted by methyl, methyl, oxo, methylamino and oxo groups at positions 3, 4, 5, 7 and 8, respectively. It was isolated from Streptomyces Sp. strain Mei37 from North Sea coast, Germany.

A member of the class of indazoles that is 4,7-dihydro-2H-indazole substituted by oxo groups at positions 4 and 7, and a methylamino group at position 5. It is produced by Streptomyces albus J1074 mutant strain.
An organic anion that is the conjugate base of dehydro-L-arabinono-1,4-lactone, arising from selective deprotonation of the 3-hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A gamma-lactone that is 5-(hydroxymethyl)furan-2(5H)-one substituted at positions 3 and 4 by hydroxy groups (the 5S-stereoisomer).
An organic anion that is the conjugate base of 2-C-methyl-D-erythritol 3,4-cyclophosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An organosulfonic acid that is propanal substituted by a sulfo group at position 3.
A member of the class of thiazepinedicarboxylic acids that is 2,5,6,7-tetrahydro-1,4-thiazepine substituted by carboxy groups at positions 3 and 5.
A member of the class of imidazopyrimidines that is imidazo[1,2-a]pyrimidine substituted by a [4-(3,4-dichlorophenyl)piperazin-1-yl]acetyl group at position 3.
